## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="f60a0-189">Lidar com o <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> eventos para fornecer sua própria <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> em vez de ter um novo <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> criado.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f60a0-189">Handle the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> event to supply your own <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> instead of having a new <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> created.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f60a0-190">Se o <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> evento não for tratado ou o manipulador não fornece uma <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext>, o <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource> cria um acordo com a configuração.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f60a0-190">If the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> event is not handled or the handler does not provide an <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext>, the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource> creates one according to its configuration.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f60a0-191">Quando um <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> é fornecido para o <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> a mesma instância do evento, é atribuída para o `Context` propriedade do objeto de evento dos eventos sucessivos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f60a0-191">When an <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> is provided to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> event, the same instance is assigned to the `Context` property of the event object of successive events.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f60a0-192">Para obter mais informações, consulte [gerenciamento de ciclo de vida do objeto de contexto (EntityDataSource)](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/67bc2486-112c-47c3-b23f-0297f7ac2160).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f60a0-192">For more information, see [Object Context Life-Cycle Management (EntityDataSource)](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/67bc2486-112c-47c3-b23f-0297f7ac2160).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f60a0-193">Para obter mais informações sobre o contexto de objeto, consulte [resolução de identidade, gerenciamento de estado e controle de alterações](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/3bd49311-0e72-4ea4-8355-38fe57036ba0).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f60a0-193">For more information about the object context, see [Identity Resolution, State Management, and Change Tracking](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/3bd49311-0e72-4ea4-8355-38fe57036ba0).</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="f60a0-194">O exemplo a seguir mostra como criar uma <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> variável do <xref:System.Web.UI.Page> do objeto e atribuí-lo para o <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSourceContextCreatingEventArgs.Context%2A> propriedade do <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSourceContextCreatingEventArgs> objeto.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f60a0-194">The following example shows how to create an <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> variable of the <xref:System.Web.UI.Page> object and assign it to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSourceContextCreatingEventArgs.Context%2A> property of the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSourceContextCreatingEventArgs> object.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public partial class _Default : System.Web.UI.Page  
    {  
        AdventureWorksModel.AdventureWorksEntities objCtx =  
            new AdventureWorksModel.AdventureWorksEntities();  
  
        protected void EntityDataSource2_ContextCreating(object sender,   
            EntityDataSourceContextCreatingEventArgs e)  
        {  
            e.Context = objCtx;  
        }  
    }  
```
